 welfare, our goal is to study the effect of the factors driving status
 with consumption.
 This is in relevance to the body of literature that points to the evidence
 of higher income-elasticities for visible items (more for goods than for
 services).
 We believe that to extend the literature on visible items to the developing
 world, one must be aware of the high price tag of some of the items that
 are deemed 
