\begin_layout Standard
We are interested in how changes in asset ownership over time relate with
 the status-signaling through non-durable consumption.
 We believe that the two pieces in the literature (on conspicuous consumption
 and on the measurement of socioeconomic status) can be understood with
 an intertemporal life-cycle model where the consumer optimises her status
 both by increasing the assets she would possess over her lifetime and different
iating herself from others through expensive non-durable consumption.
\end_layout

